27	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
28	// @ax/preset-k8s — production assembly: postgres trio + workspace-git +
29	// sandbox-k8s + claude-sdk runner.
30	//
31	// Per architecture doc Section 9, a preset is a meta-package: bumping its
32	// version ships a coordinated release of "k8s mode is now this set of plugin
33	// versions." The runtime contribution is `createK8sPlugins(config)`, which
34	// returns the assembled plugin list ready for `bootstrap()`.
35	//
36	// Why this lives in a preset and not the CLI:
37	//   - The CLI assembles the LOCAL profile (sqlite + sandbox-subprocess +
38	//     session-inmemory). That set is fine for a single laptop and the canary
39	//     test, but it can't run multi-replica because session/storage/eventbus
40	//     are in-process.
41	//   - The k8s profile swaps in the postgres trio (cross-process state),
42	//     workspace-git (durable workspace versioning), and sandbox-k8s (pods
43	//     instead of subprocesses).
44	//   - The CLI is the one place permitted to import plugins directly
45	//     (eslint allowlist); presets/** is in the same allowlist for the same
46	//     reason — they exist to compose plugins.
47	//
48	// Order matters for plugin loading. The kernel tops-sorts on declared
49	// calls/registers, but pushing in a sensible order keeps the intent obvious
50	// to readers. We mirror the CLI's order for the equivalent plugins:
51	//   1. database / storage / credentials (stateful base layer)
52	//   2. eventbus / session (cross-process coordination)
53	//   3. workspace (versioned content)
54	//   4. audit-log (subscribes to chat:end; calls storage:set)
55	//   5. http-server / auth / teams (control plane access — Week 9.5)
56	//   6. sandbox / ipc-http / llm-proxy / chat-orchestrator (chat plane)
57	//   7. tool-dispatcher → tool descriptors → mcp-client (catalog assembly)
58	//   8. agents (admin endpoints + agents:resolve gate)
59	//   9. llm-anthropic (last; everything else is in place when init runs)
60	// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
